The paper focuses on privacy-preserving schemes for ad hoc social networks, which involves security and privacy concerns. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper discusses mobile social networks (MSNs) and vehicular social networks (VSNs), which fall under the categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), respectively. The paper also examines privacy preservation models, which can be related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
